risk_json: example risk_json object returned by kwb.qmra::opencpu_simulate_risk()

Source: R/datasets.R
risk_json.Rd

JSON risk result object generated with R script (data-raw/risk_json.R)

data(risk_json)

Format

A json list with all risk results generated by opencpu_simulate_risk, using the dataset `config_json`

Examples

data("risk_json")
risk <- jsonlite::fromJSON(risk_json)
### only show "stats" elements (skip "events" and "total" due to much data)
risk_stats <- list(stats_total = risk$stats_total,
                   stats_logremoval = risk$stats_logremoval)
jsonlite::toJSON(risk_stats, pretty = TRUE)
